<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<Weakness xmlns="http://cwe.mitre.org/cwe-7" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" ID="178" Name="Improper Handling of Case Sensitivity" Abstraction="Base" Structure="Simple" Status="Incomplete">
         <Description>The product does not properly account for differences in case sensitivity when accessing or determining the properties of a resource, leading to inconsistent results.</Description>
         <Extended_Description>
            <xhtml:p>Improperly handled case sensitive data can lead to several possible consequences, including:</xhtml:p>
               <xhtml:ul>
                  <xhtml:li>case-insensitive passwords reducing the size of the key space, making brute force attacks easier</xhtml:li>
                  <xhtml:li>bypassing filters or access controls using alternate names</xhtml:li>
                  <xhtml:li>multiple interpretation errors using alternate names.</xhtml:li>
               </xhtml:ul>
         </Extended_Description>
